The paper deals with algorithms for model checking of automata, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper specifically focuses on the use of antichains to solve problems related to universality and language inclusion for nondeterministic Buchi automata, and the emptiness problem for alternating Buchi automata. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of simulation pre-orders, which is a topic that falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
